{"title_page": "List of fastest-selling products", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=November 2019}}\nThis is a '''list of the fastest-selling product''' superlatives. The definition of \"fastest-selling\" typically refers to sales results in the first week of a product's release, (i.e., which product had the biggest launch). Sometimes, rather than comparing sales figures relative to time, the target to be reached is fixed (e.g. sales at 5&nbsp;million units), and the comparison is based upon how many weeks it takes to reach it (e.g. 52 weeks vs. 56 weeks).\n\n== Books ==\n* 2007 Book \u2013 ''[[Harry Potter and the Deathly Hallows]]'' by [[J. K. Rowling]] selling approximately 15&nbsp;million copies worldwide in its first day.<ref>[http://www.worldrecordsacademy.org/business/fastest_selling_book_world_record_set_by_harry_potter_new_book_70663.htm Fastest selling book-Harry Potter final book set world record]. Worldrecordsacademy.org (July 21, 2007). Retrieved on June 1, 2014.</ref>\n* 2012 Novel \u2013 Erotica novel ''[[Fifty Shades of Grey]]'' by [[E. L. James]] selling more than 100,000 copies in its first week.<ref>[http://www.ctzine.com/twilight-inspired-erotica-becomes-fastest-selling-book-of-2012/ Twilight-Inspired Erotica Becomes Fastest Selling Book of 2012 | Cultural Transmogrifier Magazine] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20130120045437/http://www.ctzine.com/twilight-inspired-erotica-becomes-fastest-selling-book-of-2012/ |date=January 20, 2013 }}. Ctzine.com (April 30, 2012). Retrieved on June 1, 2014.</ref>\n\n== Cars ==\n* 2016 Car \u2013 [[Tesla, Inc.]] [[Tesla Model 3|Model 3]] reservations for over 180,000 units, the record for the highest single-day commitment of cars.<ref>{{cite news|url= https://www.nytimes.com/2016/04/08/business/teslas-model-3-already-has-325000-prospective-owners.html |title=Tesla's Model 3 Already Has 325,000 Preorders |work=New York Times|date=April 7, 2016 |accessdate=November 6, 2016|quote=\u201cWe are not aware of any precedent of this level of order interest for any other car,\u201d Adam Jonas, a Morgan Stanley analyst, wrote in a research note.}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Tesla's Musk: Model 3 Orders Surpassed 115,000 Within 24 Hours |first=John |last=Stoll |website=[[Wall Street Journal]] |date=February 10, 2016 |url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/teslas-musk-model-3-orders-surpassed-115-000-within-24-hours-1459483890 |accessdate=March 31, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2016-04-21/tesla-changed-cars-forever-now-it-must-deliver | title=Ten Charts That Will Make You Rethink Tesla's Model 3 | first=Tom | last=Randall | work=[[Bloomberg News]] | date=April 21, 2016 | accessdate=May 7, 2016}}</ref> 276,000 units pre-sold in the first 3 days, equivalent to {{USD|11.5 billion}}.<ref>[https://nypost.com/2016/04/04/teslas-model-3-is-smashing-sales-records Tesla's Model 3 is Smashing Sales Records]. NY Post. Retrieved on April 7, 2016.</ref><ref name=SFG02042016>{{cite news| url=http://www.sfgate.com/business/article/Tesla-Model-3-reservations-near-198-000-7223394.php| title=Tesla Model 3 reservations top 232,000 |first=David R. |last=Baker | work=[[San Francisco Chronicle]]| date=April 1, 2016| accessdate=September 14, 2016}} ''Tesla Motors had sold 107,000 Model S cars by the end of 2015''</ref><ref name=276KModel3>{{cite news| url=http://app.ft.com/cms/s/9a163366-f9de-11e5-8e04-8600cef2ca75.html | title=Tesla Model 3 orders point to potential $11.5bn sales |first=Tim |last=Bradshaw | work=[[Financial Times]] | date=April 3, 2016| accessdate=April 3, 2016}}</ref>\n* 2014 Car \u2013 [[Tesla, Inc.]] [[Tesla Model X|Model X]] having advanced sales of over $40&nbsp;million without any advertising.<ref>{{in lang|nb}} [http://www.teslamotors.com/no_NO/about/press/releases/model-x-fastest-selling-tesla-ever Model X, Fastest Selling Tesla Ever | Press Releases]. Tesla Motors. Retrieved on June 1, 2014.</ref>\n* 2012 Car (US) \u2013 [[Toyota]] [[Toyota Prius c|Prius c]] was the fastest selling car model of 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://autos.aol.com/gallery/2012-fastest-selling-cars/ |title=The Fastest Selling Cars In America |date=2012 |accessdate=June 15, 2012}}</ref>\n* 2012 Hybrid Vehicle \u2013 [[Ford Motor Company|Ford]] [[Ford C-Max|C-Max Hybrid]] is the fastest selling hybrid vehicle ever made by [[Ford]].<ref>[http://www.technologytell.com/in-car-tech/836/ford-c-max-fastest-selling-hybrid-vehicle-ever-at-launch-says-ford/ Ford C-Max \"Fastest Selling Hybrid Vehicle Ever at Launch\" Says Ford | In-Car Tech]. Technologytell.com (December 26, 2012). Retrieved on June 1, 2014.</ref>\n\n== Consumer electronics ==\n* 2017 [[Game console|Game Console]] (Japan) \u2013 [[Nintendo Switch]] selling 1.3&nbsp;million units in 1 week.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamespot.com/articles/nintendo-switch-is-nintendos-fastest-selling-conso/1100-6448486/ |title=Nintendo Switch Is Nintendo's Fastest-Selling Console Ever In The Americas, Europe, and Australia |date=March 8, 2017}}</ref>\n* 2010 Gaming Peripheral \u2013 [[Kinect]] selling 8&nbsp;million units in its first 60 days on sale.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20110311213211/http://community.guinnessworldrecords.com/_Kinect-Confirmed-As-Fastest-Selling-Consumer-Electronics-Device/blog/3376939/7691.html Kinect Confirmed As Fastest-Selling Consumer Electronics Device]. community.guinnessworldrecords.com</ref>\n* 2010 [[Operating System]] \u2013 [[Windows 7]] selling over 90&nbsp;million licenses in around 4 months.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.techspot.com/news/38121-microsoft-windows-7-is-the-fastest-selling-os-in-history-over-90-million-licenses-sold.html | title=Microsoft: Windows 7 is the fastest selling OS in history, over 90 million licenses sold | accessdate=June 15, 2012}}</ref>\n* 2010 Reader Device \u2013 [[Barnes & Noble]] Product [[Barnes & Noble Nook|Nook]] titles were sold and downloaded almost a million times on Christmas Day alone.<ref>[http://www.tabletedia.com/news/4533.html Tabletedia.com]. Tabletedia.com. Retrieved on June 1, 2014.</ref>\n\n== Music ==\n===Album===\n{{Main|Lists of fastest-selling albums}}\n*2015 Album (UK) \u2013 ''[[25 (Adele album)|25]]'' by [[Adele]] selling 800,307 units in its first week.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-34948022 |title=Adele's 25 makes UK chart history with 800,000 album sales |accessdate=November 15, 2015}}</ref>\n* 2015 Album (US) \u2013 ''[[25 (Adele album)|25]]'' by [[Adele]] selling 3,378,000 units in its first week.<ref name=\"Adele 25\"/>\n* 2015 Album (worldwide) \u2013 ''[[25 (Adele album)|25]]'' by [[Adele]] selling 3,378,000 units in its first week.<ref name=\"Adele 25\">{{cite web |url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/6770482/adele-25-other-million-selling-albums |title=Adele's '25' Is the 20th Album to Sell a Million Copies in a Week: See the Full List |accessdate=November 15, 2015}}</ref>\n* 2012 Album (UK) \u2013 ''[[Unorthodox Jukebox]]'' by [[Bruno Mars]], selling 136,000 copies in 1 week.<ref>[http://www.entertainmentwise.com/news/98677/Bruno-Mars-Scores-Fastest-Selling-UK-Album-Of-2012-With-Unorthodox-Jukebox Bruno Mars Scores Fastest-Selling UK Album Of 2012 With 'Unorthodox Jukebox' \u2013 Celebrity Gossip, News & Photos, Movie Reviews, Competitions]. Entertainmentwise (December 17, 2012). Retrieved on June 1, 2014.</ref>{{Update inline|date=June 2014}}\n* 2012 Single \u2013  ''Impossible'' by [[James Arthur]], selling 490,000 copies on 1 week.<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.theguardian.com/music/2012/dec/17/james-arthur-fastest-selling-single | location=London | work=The Guardian | title=James Arthur scores fastest-selling single of the year | date=December 17, 2012}}</ref>{{Update inline|date=June 2014}}\n* 2012 Single \u2013 ''[[Live While We're Young]]'' by [[One Direction]], reaching #1 in 40 countries immediately after pre-order release 