anchise history with over 1.0&nbsp;million units sold in its first 3 days (459,000 units in USA in 2 days).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nichegamer.com/2017/05/05/mario-kart-8-deluxe-day-one-sales-top-459000-units-in-usa/|title=Mario Kart 8 Deluxe Sales Top 459,000 Units in USA, Fastest-Selling Mario Kart Game|last=brandonthomasorselli|date=May 5, 2017|website=Niche Gamer|access-date=May 7, 2017}}</ref> \n* 2017 [[Nintendo Switch]] Game \u2013 ''[[Super Mario Odyssey]]'' shipped 2&nbsp;million units in three days.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gamespot.com/articles/super-mario-odyssey-sells-2-million-copies-in-3-da/1100-6454503/ |access-date=October 30, 2017|title=Super Mario Odyssey Crosses 2 Million Copies Sold After Only 3 Days}}</ref> \n* 2016 [[PlayStation 4]] Game \u2013 ''[[Final Fantasy XV]]'' shipped 5&nbsp;million units on its first day.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.siliconera.com/2016/12/01/final-fantasy-xv-tops-5-million-worldwide-sales-fastest-selling-title-series/|title=Final Fantasy XV Tops 5 Million In Worldwide Shipment; Fastest-Selling Title From The Series|author=|date=December 1, 2016|work=siliconera.com|access-date=December 10, 2016}}</ref>\n* 2013 video game \u2013 ''[[Grand Theft Auto V]]'' sold 12&nbsp;million units in its first day making $800&nbsp;million in sales (including pre-orders) and 16.5&nbsp;million units in three days ($1&nbsp;billion in sales).<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.gamespot.com/articles/grand-theft-auto-v-sales-reach-1-billion-in-three-days/1100-6414762/ | title=Grand Theft Auto V sales reach $1 billion in three days |date=September 20, 2013}}</ref>\n* 2013 [[Nintendo 3DS]] Game \u2013 [[Pok\u00e9mon X and Y|''Pok\u00e9mon X'' and ''Y'']] selling 4&nbsp;million units in two days.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2013/10/15/pokemon-x-and-y-sales-figures-revealed | title=Pokemon X and Y Sales Figures Revealed | date=October 15, 2013}}</ref>\n* 2012 [[PC Game]] \u2013 ''[[Diablo III]]'' selling 6.3&nbsp;mi