d\u521d\u9031500\u4e07\u672c \u636e\u3048\u7f6e\u304d\u6a5f\u5411\u3051\u3067\u6b74\u4ee3\u6700\u9ad8\u30da\u30fc\u30b9|website=\u65e5\u672c\u7d4c\u6e08\u65b0\u805e \u96fb\u5b50\u7248|language=ja|access-date=December 20, 2018}}</ref> is the fastest-selling Nintendo game of all time<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://screenrant.com/super-smash-bros-ultimate-sales-record-nintendo/|title=Super Smash Bros. Ultimate Fastest-Selling Nintendo Game of All Time|website=Screen Rant|language=en|access-date=February 1, 2019|date=January 31, 2019}}</ref> and has an all-time high record for launch-month dollars sales for a console exclusive (12&nbsp;million units sold in 3 weeks).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/MatPiscatella/status/1087852840385536000|title=Mat Piscatella on Twitter: \"US NPD SW \u2013 Super Smash Bros. Ultimate sets a new launch month dollar sales record for a platform exclusive in Video Game history, exceeding the launch month dollar sales of 2010's Halo: Reach.\"|website=Twitter|language=en|access-date=February 1, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nintendo.co.jp/ir/en/finance/software/index.html|title=Top Selling Title Sales Units|website=Nintendo|language=en|access-date=February 1, 2019}}</ref>\n* 2018 [[PlayStation 4]] and [[Xbox One]] game \u2013 [[Red Dead Redemption 2]] Shipped 10&nbsp;million units within its first two days.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2018/10/30/red-dead-redemption-2-achieves-biggest-opening-weekend-in-entertainment-history|title=Red Dead Redemption 2 Achieves Biggest Opening Weekend in Entertainment History|last=Gurwin|first=Gabe|date=October 30, 2018|website=IGN|language=en-US|access-date=October 30, 2018}}</ref>\n*2018 [[PlayStation 4]] and [[Xbox One]] Game \u2013 ''[[Monster Hunter: World]]'' shipped 5&nbsp;million units on its first three days.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.windowscentral.com/monster-hunter-world-ships-5-million-copies-over-launch-weekend | title=Monster Hunter: World ships 5 milli